==English==
===Pronunciation===
*härpo͞on, /hɑː(r)ˈpuːn/, /<tt>hA:(r)"pu:n</tt>/<!-- feels to equal stress on each syllable to me -->

===Etymology===
From Old French [[harpon]] < Latin [[harpaga]] < {{Gr.}} {{IPAchar|[[αρπαγή|ἁρπαγή]]}} (''harpagē'') "hook" < {{IPAchar|[[αρπάζω|ἁρπάζω]]}} (''harpazō'') "to snatch away, to carry off, to seize, to captivate."

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[spear]]like [[weapon]] with a [[barb]]ed [[head]] used in [[hunting]] [[whale]]s and large [[fish]]

